For comparison it may be observed that the United States
Army rifle bullet is 7 millimeters, equal 30 caliber or 0.30 inch.

The caliber of shrapnel balls varies somewhat, as do the weight and
density, but all of them were approximately ½ inch or 125 millimeters
in diameter.

The caliber of all field guns (of modern type) in the Balkan wars
were 75 millimeters, the “soixante-quinze” of the French, or about 3 inches.



